Mr. Vasanth Kumar and donor of Mrs. Vedha has been evaluated for carrier status of pathogenic variations

data.Clinical History: Mr. Y Chaitanya Krishna and Mrs. B. Keerthi Kiran are a consanguineous couple. Their first pregnancy was medically terminated at 23 weeks and 4 days of gestation in view of hydrops fetalis, short limbs, mild hydramnios and diffuse subcutaneous edema. Whole exome sequencing of the product of conception (done elsewhere, 2023) revealed a pathogenic homozygous variant GLB1:c.1479G>T (p.Lys493Asn) causative of GM1-gangliosidosis, type I/II/III/ Mucopolysaccharidosis type IVB (autosomal recessive) and two likely pathogenic heterozygous variants in BMPR1B: c.1475G>T (p.Cys492Phe) causative of Brachydactyly, type A1, D/ Brachydactyly, type A2 (autosomal dominant) and BRAF:c.2140_2145delATTGAG (p.Ile714_Glu715del) causative of Cardiofaciocutaneous syndrome/ LEOPARD syndrome 3/ Noonan syndrome 7 (autosomal dominant). Couple carrier screening by Whole Exome Sequencing (done elsewhere, 2024) revealed both partners are carriers for 3 variants of uncertain significance-GLB1:c.1479G>T, PEX7:c.508T>G, PIEZO1: c.6973A>G (autosomal recessive conditions). Additionally, Mr. Chaitanya was found to be a carrier for 2 likely pathogenic variants- DNAH7: c.1519C>T, FANCI: c.1789C>T (autosomal recessive conditions) and Mrs. Keerthi Kiran was found to be a carrier for a likely pathogenic variant KCNJ16: c.526C>T (autosomal recessive condition). Mr. Y Chaitanya Krishna and Mrs. B. Keerthi Kiran have been evaluated for carrier status of pathogenic variations.
